				\begin{document}$$ Cw=\frac{M_{S(t)}-{M}_0}{R_S\times t} $$\end{document}Cw=MSt−M0RS×twhere:
Cw = concentration (ng L−1) of analyte in water.
MS(t) = mass (ng) of analyte in Chemcatcher® receiving phase disk after exposure time t (day).
M0 = mass (ng) of analyte in receiving phase disk of Chemcatcher® field blank.
RS = sampler uptake rate of analyte (L day−1).
